# Flutter UI Conventions

## Interactive Elements Must Show Hand Cursor

Every tappable widget (`GestureDetector`, custom button) MUST be wrapped in
`MouseRegion(cursor: SystemMouseCursors.click, ...)` so the pointer changes on
hover. This applies to buttons, chips, toggles, icons, rows, and any other
element with an `onTap` / `onPressed`.

```dart
// ❌ BAD — no cursor change on hover
GestureDetector(
  onTap: _doSomething,
  child: Container(child: Text('Click me')),
)

// ✅ GOOD
MouseRegion(
  cursor: SystemMouseCursors.click,
  child: GestureDetector(
    onTap: _doSomething,
    child: Container(child: Text('Click me')),
  ),
)
```

**Exception:** Full-screen scrims / barriers used only to dismiss overlays do
NOT need the click cursor (they are dismissal zones, not buttons).

If a `MouseRegion` already exists for hover tracking (`onEnter`/`onExit`), add
`cursor: SystemMouseCursors.click` to that same region instead of nesting
another.

## Color Opacity

Use `.withValues(alpha: 0.5)` instead of the deprecated `.withOpacity(0.5)`.

## Linting

The project uses `analysis_options.yaml` at the repo root (not inside
`phonegentic/`). Key rules to respect:

- `always_specify_types` — annotate all local variables, parameters, return types.
- `prefer_single_quotes` — use `'` unless the string contains a single quote.
- `sort_constructors_first` — constructors before fields/methods.
- `use_super_parameters` — prefer `{super.key}` over `Key? key) : super(key: key)`.
- `unnecessary_getters_setters` — expose fields directly when no logic is needed.

Run `flutter analyze` from `phonegentic/` before considering any change done.

